(a poem)
Only one more month of 2022
the year began with a clear vision and view
what I would be and what I would do

hit a bump
stumble back
brush off the dust
get back on track
wash rinse repeat
until you realize that
you took 1 step forward
and 3 steps back

Is the world really ending or is it just me
2022’s favorite hot mess nominee

how I got here
I do not know
say I’m not superstitious
but I still tiptoe
over every root and sidewalk crack

It’s not destination ideal me
you only find yourself here after lost at sea
once you’ve accepted the ocean’s lack of predictability

so cheers to all the dead storylines
of people I thought
I’d one day be
this time around I’ll surrender to 2023

Problem solving on the wall with @prAna.
In order to figure out this sequence I needed to:
 
1. Keep an open mind and assess my options. I ended up crimping a right hand below a more obviously chalked hold. It was smaller but had more bite. I also found an undercling that really helped me get over my left heel hook.
 
2. Fall. After falling enough times I was able to relax into a flow and move more efficiently
 
3. (my favorite part) Put all the pieces together!
 
This is generally how I break things down when trying an unfamiliar climb. Sometimes climbing feels more like a puzzle than a sport. Do you have a system for when you get stuck? Please share any tips below!
 
#prAnaPartner

It’s been hard to give any updates as my state of health has been rather volatile. I am back in the hospital for now. I am finally receiving some of the medicines I’ve needed (but been struggling to get outpatient) and we are reassessing our current line of treatment.
This time I can get up and see out my window though :) I hope you all enjoy how the glow of the sun rise seems to make red brick come alive.
I will give you all updates when I have em. 🤍

Update!

I will share a more through update when I have more energy.
Thank you for all the love and support 🤍

A little recovery update:
I have had a lot of people assuming I am “recovered” and congratulating me.. I appreciate the enthusiasm for my perceived wellness, but just keep in mind that is not something you can see entirely from simple highlights on the internet. I have obviously come a very long way, but I just want to clarify that I am still dealing with a lot of symptoms. Luckily my many medications have been making the symptoms manageable most days.
A few weeks following my last hospital visit, I was doing really well and I began bouldering again. I recently had to stop because the impact became too much and started aggravating symptoms again. Yesterday I decided to do a very short (no impact, all down climbing) bouldering session and I was able to do this! 📈
I still have not gotten the hip surgeries I need because god knows why. Communication between insurance and several doctors takes longer than it ought to. There also seems to be some disagreement between my doctors about the safety of the surgery while on certain medications.
I am so happy I am at the level of functioning I am at, but I also can’t wait to eventually be pain free, and have the energy I used to. Thank you all for the support through this crazy journey 🤍

Here are my last couple months of recovery,
if it was going fastly but not-certainly.
🐢 
Life right now is a lot of sleep and trying to tell my leg to move. I’m healing well and almost entirely off of the crutches!
Milestones I hit in this time:
- learning to walk for the 3rd time 🫠
- graduating from the walker
- graduating to just one crutch 🩼
- walking mochi all the way around the block
- starting some mellow no-impact climbing
- weighting a harness ^

It’s been really wild to watch the anniversaries of my illness pass.
Oh 1 year ago I started feeling dizzy
1year ago I knew I was sick
1year ago I got a diagnosis..
etc.
I’m not much of a musician, but I would say I am a writer. I wrote this on the 1 year anniversary of when my first symptoms first began.  I’m so happy that I’m in a far more stable place with managing symptoms. 🤞 we’re always moving forward.
So 🥂 to anyone and everyone listening to this who has every had their own life turned upside down.
